	NAME
		WA+A WA_A WA(A) WAA FA
	NOTE
		The signs combining wa with various vowels are used only in foreign words, so they probably represent a non-Hittite sound. Hurrian scholars traditionally transcribe these with a w, but since it's clearly not the Hittite w, I assign them the readings fa, fe, fi, fo, fu. Similarly ap, ip, up get the readings af, if, uf.
